benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/block - Block an account

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC18, @TC21, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC27 cover successful blocking with valid data and various optional parameters.
Invalid Payload: @TC10 covers malformed JSON; @TC14 covers malicious payload; @TC07 covers invalid accountId format.
Missing Data: @TC05 covers no prior blocking states; @TC09 covers missing request body.
Non-Existent Account: @TC06 covers account not found.
Authorization: @TC08, @TC11, @TC12, @TC14, @TC22, @TC24, @TC27 cover missing or invalid authorization/authentication.
Edge Cases: @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC18, @TC20, @TC26 cover maximum/minimum field lengths, large payloads, high concurrency, and resource utilization.
Plugin Interaction: @TC21 and @TC22 cover plugin property triggers and plugin service unavailability.
Regression Tests: @TC23 and @TC24 ensure previously fixed issues and backward compatibility.
Performance: @TC19 and @TC20 test slow responses, large payloads, and high concurrency.
Security: @TC13 and @TC14 test SQL injection and malicious payloads.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios test system behavior under rapid or repeated requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Concurrency Race Conditions: No explicit tests for race conditions beyond high concurrency performance.
Soft Deletes or Data Retention: No tests for soft delete behavior or data recovery.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling to ensure large dataset responses are managed correctly.
Include rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system stability under load.
Implement tests to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Create explicit race condition tests for concurrent updates or deletions.
Add scenarios for soft delete behavior and data recovery if applicable.
